definition.value: An  EC 2.7.3.* (phosphotransferases with a nitrogenous group as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of creatine kinase, EC 2.7.3.2.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-leucine, and two L-aspartic acid units joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A heterodetic cyclic peptide that is a cyclic enkephalin analogue, having D-penicillaminyl residues located at positions 2 and 5, which form the heterocycle via a disulfide bond.

A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between the carboxy group of phenylacetic acid and the secodary amino group of (5R,7S,8S)-N-methyl-7-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)-1-oxaspiro[4.5]decan-8-amine.

A monocarboxylic acid amide obtained by formal condensation between the carboxy group of 3,4-dichlorophenylacetic acid and the secondary amino group of (1R,2R)-N-methyl-2-(pyrrolidin-1-yl)cyclohexanamine
An aldehyde of general formula R-CH2-CH=O in which the aldehydic C=O function is attached to a CH2 group at the alpha-position.
Any EC 3.4.11.* (aminopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of methionyl aminopeptidase (EC 3.4.11.18).
Any methionyl aminopeptidase inhibitor that inhibits the action of methionyl aminopeptidase 2.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-leucine, L-aspartic acid and glycine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, two L-leucine units, and L-aspartic acid joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetralin substituted at positions 1 and 7 by hydroxy and dipropylamino groups respectively
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, two L-leucine units, and an L-histidine joined in sequence.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, two L-leucine units, and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, two L-leucine units, and L-threonine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
An indole that is 1H-indole substituted at positions 2, 3 and 7 by cyano, iodo and 3-(tert-butylamino)-2-hydroxypropoxy groups respectively.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-leucine, L-threonine, and L-glutamine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A metalloporphyrin obtained by formal dehydrogenation across positions 7 and 8 of cobalt-precorrin-3.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-leucine, L-valine, and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-methionine, L-serine, and L-arginine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-phenylalanine, L-threonine, and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A member of the class of ergot alkaloids that is known to act on serotonin and dopamine receptors.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-phenylalanine, L-tryptophan, and L-asparagine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.

An indolyl carboxylate ester obtained by formal condensation between the carboxy group of 1-methylindole-3-carboxylic acid with the hydroxy group of N-{2-[4-(hydroxymethyl)piperidin-1-yl]ethyl}methanesulfonamide.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-threonine, L-alanine, and L-proline joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-tryptophan, L-asparagine, and L-aspartic acid joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-valine, L-aspartic acid, and L-histidine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-valine, L-aspartic acid, and L-proline joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-valine, L-aspartic acid, and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.

A 1-benzothiophene that is 1-benzothiophene-4,7-dione bearing additional methylthio and 3,7,11,15,19,23-hexamethyltetracosyl substituents at positions 5 and 6 respectively. Isolated from Caldariella acidophila.
A 1-benzothiophene that is 1-benzothiophene-4,7-diol bearing additional methylthio and 3,7,11,15,19,23-hexamethyltetracosyl substituents at positions 5 and 6 respectively
An  L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of O-ureido-L-serine.
A progestin consisting of 17beta-propionylestra-4,9-dien-3-one substituted at position 17 by a methyl group.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-valine, L-aspartic acid, and L-tyrosine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-alanine, L-valine, and two L-proline units joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide composed of L-alanine and L-proline joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of L-alanine and L-serine joined by a peptide linkage.
A dipeptide composed of L-alanine and L-tyrosine joined by a peptide linkage.
An organic heteromonocyclic ring consisting of one oxygen atom and four carbon atoms.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-arginine, L-asparagine, L-glutamine, and L-arginine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A mancude heterobicyclic organic group consisting of a benzene ring fused to a pyrrole ring.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-arginine, L-asparagine, glycine, and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
An organic heterobicyclic group derived from indolizidine.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-arginine, L-lysine, L-cysteine, and glycine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-arginine, two L-phenylalanine units and L-cysteine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
An organic group derived from allene.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-arginine, L-threonine and two L-cysteine units joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A tetrapeptide composed of L-arginine, L-tryptophan, L-serine, and L-tyrosine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A dipeptide formed from two L-asparagine units.
A tetrapeptide composed of two L-asparagine units, L-proline and L-serine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
